earn to think independently&quot; No, you want them to learn to think like you with no other influence, because, if it was really about independent thought, they could go to school, and then, at home you could teach them your revolutionary ideals which Big Brother doesn't want them to learn. &#10;Home Schooling is about the narrowing of the mind not the broadening. However no-one has made it illegal, and the checks are a good idea for kids that would otherwise be invisible. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="764" language="en" documentId="915" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="MiddleEnglandLefty" date="06 November 2009 3:55pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6745123" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="2" thumbsDown="0" origId="915" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="195"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="196" end="276"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="277" end="582"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="583" end="764"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>